Title: 1122 DEC Network Equipment
Description:
Nottingham Trent University (NTU) are constructing an exciting new Enterprise Innovation Centre (EIC) within the heart of the City of Nottingham. The EIC will form a major building block of the University's Enterprise Action Plan and will be a key enabler of many elements within the University's strategic plan - Creating the University of the Future.

The Enterprise Innovation Centre (EIC) project is part funded by the European Regional Development Fund (ERDF). The project supports research and innovation, enhancing the competitiveness of SMEs and the shift towards a low carbon economy.
When opened, the Centre will be known as The Dryden Enterprise Centre (DEC).

Nottingham Trent University have a significant investment of exiting networking equipment deployed across the Campus locations providing a seamless service to end users. Whilst the Dryden Enterprise Centre (DEC) differs from our typical deployment, we wish to utilise the same common networking platforms and configurations to ease ongoing maintenance and support functions. This tender is therefore limited to the supply of the required equipment only, we do not require consultancy, configuration or installation of the equipment. These tasks will be performed by the existing NTU appropriately skilled engineers.

Title: CA4817 - Software Licenses & Associated Services for Academies & Schools
Description:
This is a re-tender of the current Software Licenses - Academies & Schools framework which was originally tendered for at the beginning of 2014 and launched to CPC members in July 2014.  The new framework will be available to all Schools & Academies who are CPC members https://www.thecpc.ac.uk/members/regions.php.  The new framework will be split into 4 lots and will run for an initial duration of 2 years with the option to extend by two possible one year extensions.  CPC Membership is open to the entire Education Sector, details of which are available here: https://www.gov.uk/guidance/get-information-about-schools

Includes Lots: 
Lot 4: One Stop Shop
Lot 3: Other off the Shelf Software
Lot 1: Microsoft
Lot 2: Adobe

To access this competition: 

Registered:
Login to https://suppliers.multiquote.com and view the opportunity CA4817.

Not registered:
Visit https://suppliers.multiquote.com then register and quote CA4817 as the reason for registration. 

 Any queries please contact MultiQuote on 0151 482 9230.

Title: RM1054 Technology Products
Description:
Crown Commercial Service as the Contracting Authority has put in place a Pan Government Collaborative Framework Agreement for Technology Products for use by UK public sector bodies (and any future successors to these organisations), which include Central Government Departments and their Arm's Length Bodies and Agencies, Non Departmental Public Bodies, NHS bodies and Local Authorities. Crown Commercial Service reserves the right for an electronic auction to be held by public sector bodies during further competition among the parties to the Framework Agreement.

Contract Notice reference 2014/S 093-162738 dated 15/05/2014 explains how the range of products covered by this Framework Agreement has been broken down into Lots. This Contract Notice has been included as one of the attachments.

The Contract End Date stated earlier takes into account that the Crown Commercial Service has the option of extending the duration by a  maximum of 2 years. The option to extend can  be taken up on the expiry of the initial 2 year contract period.
